<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-05-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-05-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="420" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d420">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 24595/6.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Monroe</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">San
                                    Jose</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-05-18"><hi rend="italic">May 18,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Monroe says Red Cross idea as to providing shelter is excellent, and
                            that there is urgent necessity of houses 24 by 16 feet with siding of
                            ordinary lumber, with light weight, corrugated iron roofs.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>